Business Brief -- Roadway Services Inc.:
   Contract Is Signed to Buy
   Cole Enterprises Common
Roadway Services, an Akron, Ohio, motor freight carrier,
said the transaction is subject to approval by the Interstate
Commerce Commission and other bodies.
   Cole will continue to be operated by its current
management, Roadway Services said. Once the regulatory
approvals are obtained, Coles Express will become part of
Roadway Services' regional carrier group. Other carriers in
the regional group include Viking Freight System, serving the
west, and Spartan Express, serving the south and central
states.
   Cole Enterprises had 1991 revenue of $31.9 million. Coles
Express serves customers in Maine, Massachusetts, New
Hampshire and Vermont.
   Cole Enterprises' headquarters will remain in Bangor,
Maine.